<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,901,1754]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,1369,1394]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis (worker).</emphasis>
This species is characterized by a short antennal scape; a petiolar node in lateral view thick and trapezoid, with a slightly convex posterior margin; a subpetiolar process with large fenestra and large teeth; and its third abdominal tergum as long as broad. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="1986" box="[768,990,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiponensis">
